body.name: MOROVOL PC Case ATX Pre-Install 4x120mm RGB Fans(Fix Color), ATX Gaming PC Case, USB 3.0 Tempered Glass Mid Tower Computer Case, Black,R7
features: Cost-effective PC Case -- MOROVOL R7 comes pre-installed with four fix color RGB fans; the gaming case is equipped with two pieces of tempered glass, high light transmission performance can showcase the cool lights of the case; the mid tower case can adapt to the needs of different players' PC components

4 Fix Color RGB Fans - The R7 pc case is pre-installed with 4 RGB 120mm case fans, which are fixed RGB lighting capable and can provide considerable airflow to enhance cooling. (Note: The lighting is fixed, not addressable.)

Show off your lights - The R7 gaming case features a stylish tempered glass design with natural light transmission to show off your toy artifacts, PC components and cool RGB lights. The highly transparent glass on the side and front will help you build the coolest computer case. In addition, the tempered glass is hard, not easily damaged and soundproof, providing great comfort for office/gaming environments!

Well-designed Airflow - MOROVOL PC case is pre-installed with 4 120mm RGB fans to provide lighting, utilizing anti-vortex blades to ensure proper airflow inside the case for better cooling performance than regular computer cases. The front panel side honeycomb mesh is designed for precise air intake, and with the case fans keeps the PC at a stable performance.
Powerful I/O panel - The gaming PC case has 1 USB 3.0 high-speed port, 2 USB 2.0 ports, HD audio and microphone ports. Dedicated LED buttons can be used to control 19 lighting modes for ARGB fans.

Suitable Size Capacity - ATX case is compatible with most PC hardware in the market, the right size will not occupy too much desktop space. Package includes: R7 case*1, RGB fan*4, manual*1, screw accessories*1 (motherboard, graphics card, power supply, cooler not included).

No Risk of Purchase - If you have any problems with your case, please feel free to contact us by clicking "S0ld-by-MOROVOL" on the page and we will try our best to help you! MOROVOLstrives to provide the best support to our customers!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 21, 2023
reviews.reviewText: So I game a few hours every day and it was time to upgrade my pc and I went with an ATX motherboard instead of my micro ATX board so I needed a new case to make the fit. There are a lot of a different cases out there for all kinds of prices but this one is a solid budget choice. The case is super solid, it looks great, and it comes with 4 fans. You really can’t beat that. All fans and lights were in working order. Running the wires was easy enough maybe some changes there could make it easier but over all this case is fantastic. Solid 10/10

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice little case.
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I bought this case for my son's custom build that we did together. It was plenty roomy, and has lots of space for additional fans (we opted to use 6, AsiaHorse fans instead of the included ones.Cable management was excellent. Easy to use, easy to install the MOBO and GPU.I would highly recommend this case for the novice, or experienced builder. My only complaint would be that it only allows for 2, 120mm top mounted fans, but other than that, it's a cool little case, and looks incredible!His setup is:• MSI MAG B650 Mortar, MATX, WiFi Motherboard.• AMD Ryzen 5-7600, 6 Core, 12 thread, CPU.• NVIDIA 3060ti GPU.• 1TB SSD.• 32gb T Force Delta DDR5 6000MHz RAM.• 700w, Cooler Master power supply.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 18, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Space saving and easy to work with
reviews.reviewText: I’ll start by saying that I am a fan of the micro ATX form factor in general. I think it's the most utilitarian form factor in production and it's sad that it's so ignored. When most PC's now are a motherboard, an attached SSD, a graphics card and a heat-sink, I don't know why people are still buying gigantic desk monsters. ITX is very efficient and elegant is also expensive and limiting. A four terabyte 3.5” drive can be had for $50 these days. A 4tb SSD still clocks in close to $400. Until that changes, a 3.5” drive bay is still a must IMHO. This case is a great size. The depth is a little lower than a lot of matx cases so you can’t fit a long GPU in here (240mm is probably the max…) but most folks building with this aren’t going to be putting a 3090 in it anyway. You will probably want to stick with a shorter PSU as well. This case was easy to work in. It has all the access you would typically find in a modern case. Honestly, my biggest gripe is that it should include a rear fan to match the front ones. The RGB/Fan controller has a port for a third one but it’s proprietary and I could not find one anywhere. Just charge another $5 and include the rear fan. PWM control would be nice as well…Pros:Great space saving case without being too small.Cable management is surprisingly goodThe case feels well put together and not cheaply madeThe front panel pops off easily for access to the fans.Cons:Depth is lower then many MATX cases. PSU and GPU sizes will be limitedNo rear fanNo PWM controlFans aren’t loud, but they aren’t quiet either

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice case for the money
reviews.reviewText: Check your motherboard and order the led controller of your motherboard doesn’t have the correct plug. Mine didn’t, part is like $10-$15 bucks.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great starter gaming PC build
reviews.reviewText: I'm just getting into PC gaming and this seems like the perfect start for my build. It already has 4 fans installed from the start. The tempered glass is going to make the rgb look real nice when I'm finally finished. All the cables are neatly bundled in the metal side of the case with the connectors easily accessible to run to the connections whenever they arrive. I just wish there was a way to contact the seller so I could find out what rgb adapter I need since my motherboard is a 4 pin. Also nothing came damaged, dinted or scratched. The only bad thing I can say is that it was sent in just the main box. I live in a apartment complex and anyone who happened to walk by could see what it was.**Edit**I found the way to communicate with the seller and I was given quick responses with multiple ways and product suggestions on how to address my problem with the rgb fans to make them work with my motherboard. Click on their name on sold by.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 6, 2023
reviews.reviewText: It is for sure a case. The one got ya is the hardware bag is hidden in the back of the 3.5” drive bays. Took me a few minutes to find the screws to secure the mother board. Otherwise cable management ect was what you should expect in a sub 100$ case.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I was about 8-10 feet away from it and I could hear it absolutely blaring. I was running elden ring on max settings so it gets my 6700xt up to around 75c and my god do this fans make noise. If u don’t mind it sure get it but I was playing with my ear buds in and even past the noise of the game I could hear these fans next to me. I personally don’t recommend and I have switched the front 3 out with noctua fans and it is now much more manageable. Don’t recommend for noise but as far is the build went it was pretty okay.
